21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
23 Article – State Government
24 9–901.
25 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
26 (b) “Active duty” has the meaning stated in 37 U.S.C. § 101.
27 (c) “ACTIVE MILITARY, NAVAL, AIR, OR SPACE SERVICE” HAS THE MEANING
28 STATED IN 38 U.S.C. § 101.
29 (D) “Active service member” means an individual who is:
30 (1) an active duty member of the uniformed services; or
31 (2) serving in a reserve component of the uniformed services on active duty
32 orders.
33 [(d)] (E) “Armed forces” has the meaning stated in 10 U.S.C. § 101.

SENATE BILL 194 3
1 [(e)] (F) “Board” means the Board of Trustees of the Maryland Veterans Trust.
2 [(f)] (G) “Department” means the Department of Veterans and Military
3 Families.
4 [(g)] (H) “Military family” includes the spouse and dependent children of a
5 service member or veteran related by blood, marriage, or adoption.
6 [(h)] (I) “Reserve component” has the meaning stated in 37 U.S.C. § 101.
7 [(i)] (J) “Secretary” means the Secretary of Veterans and Military Families.
8 [(j)] (K) “Service member” means an individual who is a member of:
9 (1) the uniformed services; or
10 (2) a reserve component of the uniformed services.
11 [(k)] (L) “Trust” means the Maryland Veterans Trust.
12 [(l)] (M) “Uniformed services” has the meaning stated in 37 U.S.C. § 101.
13 [(m)] (N) Except as otherwise provided in this subtitle, “veteran” has the
14 meaning stated in 38 U.S.C. § 101.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
16 as follows:
17 Article – Economic Development
18 6–301.
19 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
20 (e) “Qualified veteran employee” means an individual who:
21 (1) is honorably discharged or released under honorable circumstances
22 from active military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service as defined in [38 U.S.C. § 101] §
23 9–901 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE; and
24 (1) IS A VETERAN; AND
25 (2) is a qualified veteran as defined under § 51(d)(3)(A) of the Internal
26 Revenue Code for purposes of the federal Work Opportunity Tax Credit.

4 SENATE BILL 194
1 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
2 as follows:
3 Article – Tax – Property
4 1–101.
5 (a) In this article the following words have the meanings indicated.
6 (A–2) “ACTIVE MILITARY, NAVAL, AIR, OR SPACE SERVICE” HAS THE MEANING
7 STATED IN § 9–901 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.
8 [(a–2)] (A–3) “Active service member” has the meaning stated in § 9–901 of the
9 State Government Article.
10 7–208.
11 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
12 (2) “Disabled active duty service member” means an individual in active
13 [service of the] military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service [as defined in 38 U.S.C. § 101]
14 who has a service connected physical disability that:
15 (i) is reasonably certain to continue for the life of the service
16 member; and
17 (ii) was not caused or incurred by misconduct of the service member.
18 (3) (i) “Disabled veteran” means an individual who:
19 1. is honorably discharged or released under honorable
20 circumstances from active military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service [as defined in 38
21 U.S.C. § 101]; and
22 1. IS A VETERAN; AND
23 2. has been declared by the U.S. Department of Veterans
24 Affairs to have a permanent 100% service connected disability that results from blindness
25 or other disabling cause that:
26 A. is reasonably certain to continue for the life of the veteran;
27 and
28 B. was not caused or incurred by misconduct of the veteran.

SENATE BILL 194 5
1 (ii) “Disabled veteran” includes an individual who qualifies
2 posthumously for a 100% service connected disability.
3 (4) “Dwelling house”:
4 (i) means real property that is:
5 1. the legal residence of a disabled active duty service
6 member, disabled veteran, or surviving spouse; and
7 2. occupied by not more than 2 families; and
8 (ii) includes the lot or curtilage and structures necessary to use the
9 real property as a residence.
10 (5) “Individual who died in the line of duty” means an individual who died
11 while in the active military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service [of the United States] as a
12 result of an injury or disease that is deemed under 38 U.S.C. § 105 to have been incurred
13 in the line of duty.
14 (6) “Surviving spouse” means an individual who has not remarried and
15 who:
16 (i) is the surviving spouse of a disabled veteran;
17 (ii) is the surviving spouse of an individual who died in the line of
18 duty; or
19 (iii) receives Dependency and Indemnity Compensation from the U.S.
20 Department of Veterans Affairs.
21 (d) (1) A disabled veteran or a surviving spouse of a disabled veteran shall
22 apply for an exemption under this section by providing to the supervisor:
23 (i) a copy of the disabled veteran’s discharge certificate from active
24 military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service; and
25 (ii) 1. on the form provided by the Department, a certification of
26 the disabled veteran’s disability from the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs; or
27 2. a rating decision of the disabled veteran’s disability from
28 the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs that includes the effective date of the rating
29 decision.
30 9–265.
31 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.

6 SENATE BILL 194
1 (2) “Disabled veteran” means an individual who:
2 (i) is honorably discharged or released under honorable
3 circumstances from active military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service [as defined in 38
4 U.S.C. § 101]; and
5 (I) IS A VETERAN; AND
6 (ii) 1. has been declared by the U.S. Department of Veterans
7 Affairs to have a permanent service–connected disability of at least 50% that results from
8 blindness or any other disabling cause that:
9 A. is reasonably certain to continue for the life of the veteran;
10 and
11 B. was not caused or incurred by misconduct of the veteran;
12 or
13 2. has been declared by the U.S. Department of Veterans
14 Affairs to have a nonpermanent service–connected disability of 100% that results from
15 blindness or any other disabling cause that was not caused or incurred by misconduct of
16 the veteran.
17 (d) (1) A disabled veteran shall apply for the property tax credit under this
18 section by providing to the county or municipal corporation:
19 (i) a copy of the disabled veteran’s discharge certificate from active
20 military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service; and
21 (ii) on the form provided by the county or municipal corporation, a
22 certification of the disabled veteran’s disability from the U.S. Department of Veterans
23 Affairs.
24 9–323.
25 (g) (1) (i) In this subsection the following words have the meanings
26 indicated.
27 (ii) 1. “Disabled veteran” means an individual who:
28 A. is honorably discharged or released under honorable
29 circumstances from active military, naval, [or] air, OR SPACE service [as defined in 38
30 U.S.C. § 101]; and
31 A. IS A VETERAN; AND

SENATE BILL 194 7
1 B. has been declared by the U.S. Department of Veterans
2 Affairs to have a permanent service–connected disability that results from blindness or
3 other disabling cause that:
4 I. is reasonably certain to continue for the life of the veteran;
5 and
6 II. was not caused or incurred by misconduct of the veteran.
7 2. “Disabled veteran” includes an individual who qualifies
8 posthumously for a service–connected disability.
9 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 2 of this Act shall be
10 applicable to all taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.
11 SECTION 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 3 of this Act shall be
12 applicable to all taxable years beginning after June 30, 2026.
13 SECTION 6. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
14 1, 2026.
